      • flatten_parameters

        public void flatten_parameters()
        Modifies the internal storage of weights for optimization purposes. On CPU, this method should be called if any of the weight or bias vectors are changed (i.e. weights are added or removed). On GPU, it should be called __any time the storage of any parameter is modified__, e.g. any time a parameter is assigned a new value. This allows using the fast path in cuDNN implementations of respective RNN forward() methods. It is called once upon construction, inside reset().
